Cockroach
====

Cockroach is a probe utility. It can measure execution time of functions
or a part of programs. It also can insert userdefined probes dynamically.

==============================
How to build
==============================
$ ./autogen.sh
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make install

==============================
How to run
==============================
$ LDPRELOAD=cockroach.so COCKROACH_RECIPE=<path>/recipe_file program args

==============================
Format of recipe file
==============================
# Meausre execution time: T dll_name symbol|offset(hex)
T libc.so memset
T libc.so 0000000000053840

# Probes: P dll_name symbol|offset(hex) probe_so probe_name
P libc.so printf myprobe.so my_probe

==============================
Recipe command
==============================
T: Time Measurement [64bit aboslute jumper (overwrite 13B)]
t: Time Measurement [32bit relative jumper (overwrite 5B). rarely fails] <Not implemented>
P: User define probe [64bit aboslute jumper (overwrite 13B)] <Not implemented>
p: User define probe [32bit relative jumper (overwrite 5B). rarely fails] <Not implemented>
